# Configuration Files

## channels.json

Primary config file at `config/channels.json`. Deserialized with `System.Text.Json`.

### Schema

```json
{
  "comPort": "COM5",
  "baudRate": 9600,
  "protocol": "lcus_a",
  "exclusive": true,
  "channels": {
    "red": 1,
    "yellow": 2,
    "green": 3,
    "buzzer": 4
  },
  "statusEngine": {
    "pollIntervalMinutes": 3,
    "warningThresholdMinutes": 60,
    "criticalThresholdMinutes": 120,
    "hysteresisPolls": 2,
    "buzzerPulseMs": 750
  }
}
```

### Field Notes

- `comPort`: Windows COM port name. Overridden by `--port` CLI flag.
- `protocol`: `"lcus_a"` or `"lcus_b"`. Overridden by `--protocol` CLI flag.
- `exclusive`: When true, only one color channel (1-3) can be on at a time. Buzzer (ch 4) is independent.
- `channels`: Maps logical names to physical relay channel numbers (1-4). Code should never hardcode channel meanings.
- `statusEngine`: Only used by the status engine process (Phase 2-3). `hysteresisPolls` = number of consecutive polls a condition must hold before state transitions.

### C# Model

Create a strongly-typed `BeaconConfig` class in BeaconCtl.Core. Use `JsonPropertyName` attributes matching the camelCase keys above.
